Gets a specific network object.

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        The `network` key contains the network

    + Attributes (Networks Response1)



### Update a Network [PUT]
Updates the network properties.

Note that when updating labels, the network’s current set of labels will be replaced with the labels provided in the request body. So, for example, if you want to add a new label, you have to provide all existing labels plus the new label in the request body.

Note: if the network object changes during the request, the response will be a “conflict” error.

+ Request (<<Add Header Value>>)

    + Attributes (UpdateNetworkRequest)



+ Response 200 (application/json)

        The `network` key contains the updated network

    + Attributes (Networks Response1)


    + Body

            {"network":{"created":"2016-01-30T23:50:00+00:00","id":4711,"ip_range":"10.0.0.0/16","labels":{"labelkey":"value"},"load_balancers":[42],"name":"new-name","protection":{"delete":false},"routes":[{"destination":"10.100.1.0/24","gateway":"10.0.1.1"}],"servers":[42],"subnets":[{"gateway":"10.0.0.1","ip_range":"10.0.1.0/24","network_zone":"eu-central","type":"cloud"}]}}




