# Data Structures

## ActionsResponse (object)


### Properties
+ `actions` (array[Action], required) 
+ `meta` (Meta, optional) 


## Action (object)


### Properties
+ `command`: `start_server` (string, required) - Command executed in the Action
+ `error` (Error, required, nullable) - Error message for the Action if error occurred, otherwise null
+ `finished`: `2016-01-30T23:55:00+00:00` (string, required, nullable) - Point in time when the Action was finished (in ISO-8601 format). Only set if the Action is finished otherwise null.
+ `id`: `42` (number, required) - ID of the Resource
+ `progress`: `100` (number, required) - Progress of Action in percent
+ `resources` (array[Resource], required) - Resources the Action relates to
+ `started`: `2016-01-30T23:55:00+00:00` (string, required) - Point in time when the Action was started (in ISO-8601 format)
+ `status` (enum[string], required) - Status of the Action
    + `success`
    + `running`
    + `error`


## Error (object)
Error message for the Action if error occurred, otherwise null

### Properties
+ `code`: `action_failed` (string, required) - Fixed machine readable code
+ `message`: `Action failed` (string, required) - Humanized error message


## Resource (object)


### Properties
+ `id`: `42` (number, required) - ID of the Resource
+ `type`: `server` (string, required) - Type of resource referenced


## Meta (object)


### Properties
+ `pagination` (Pagination, required) 


## Pagination (object)


### Properties
+ `last_page`: `4` (number, required, nullable) - ID of the last page available. Can be null if the current page is the last one.
+ `next_page`: `4` (number, required, nullable) - ID of the next page. Can be null if the current page is the last one.
+ `page`: `3` (number, required) - Current page number
+ `per_page`: `25` (number, required) - Maximum number of items shown per page in the response
+ `previous_page`: `2` (number, required, nullable) - ID of the previous page. Can be null if the current page is the first one.
+ `total_entries`: `100` (number, required, nullable) - The total number of entries that exist in the database for this query. Nullable if unknown.


## ActionResponse (object)


### Properties
+ `action` (Action, required) 


## CertificatesResponse (object)


### Properties
+ `certificates` (array[Certificate], required) 
+ `meta` (Meta, optional) 


## Certificate (object)


### Properties
+ `certificate`: `-----BEGIN CERTIFICATE-----
...` (string, required, nullable) - Certificate and chain in PEM format, in order so that each record directly certifies the one preceding
+ `created`: `2016-01-30T23:55:00+00:00` (string, required) - Point in time when the Resource was created (in ISO-8601 format)
+ `domain_names`: `["example.com","webmail.example.com","www.example.com"]` (array[string], required) - Domains and subdomains covered by the Certificate
+ `fingerprint`: `03:c7:55:9b:2a:d1:04:17:09:f6:d0:7f:18:34:63:d4:3e:5f` (string, required, nullable) - SHA256 fingerprint of the Certificate
+ `id`: `42` (number, required) - ID of the Resource
+ `labels` (string, required) - User-defined labels (key-value pairs)
+ `name`: `my-resource` (string, required) - Name of the Resource. Must be unique per Project.
+ `not_valid_after`: `2019-07-08T09:59:59+00:00` (string, required, nullable) - Point in time when the Certificate stops being valid (in ISO-8601 format)
+ `not_valid_before`: `2019-01-08T10:00:00+00:00` (string, required, nullable) - Point in time when the Certificate becomes valid (in ISO-8601 format)
+ `status` (Status2, optional, nullable) - Current status of a type `managed` Certificate, always *null* for type `uploaded` Certificates
+ `type` (enum[string], optional) - Type of the Certificate
    + `uploaded`
    + `managed`
+ `used_by` (array[UsedBy], required) - Resources currently using the Certificate


## Status2 (object)
Current status of a type `managed` Certificate, always *null* for type `uploaded` Certificates

### Properties
+ `error` (Error2, optional, nullable) - If issuance or renewal reports `failed`, this property contains information about what happened
+ `issuance` (enum[string], optional) - Status of the issuance process of the Certificate
    + `pending`
    + `completed`
    + `failed`
+ `renewal` (enum[string], optional) - Status of the renewal process of the Certificate.
    + `scheduled`
    + `pending`
    + `failed`
    + `unavailable`


## Error2 (object)
If issuance or renewal reports `failed`, this property contains information about what happened

### Properties
+ `code` (string, optional) 
+ `message` (string, optional) 


## UsedBy (object)


### Properties
+ `id`: `4711` (number, required) - ID of resource referenced
+ `type`: `load_balancer` (string, required) - Type of resource referenced


## CreateCertificateRequest (object)


### Properties
+ `certificate`: `-----BEGIN CERTIFICATE-----
...` (string, optional) - Certificate and chain in PEM format, in order so that each record directly certifies the one preceding. Required for type `uploaded` Certificates.
+ `domain_names` (array[string], optional) - Domains and subdomains that should be contained in the Certificate issued by *Let's Encrypt*. Required for type `managed` Certificates.
+ `labels` (object, optional) - User-defined labels (key-value pairs)
+ `name`: `my website cert` (string, required) - Name of the Certificate
+ `private_key`: `-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----
...` (string, optional) - Certificate key in PEM format. Required for type `uploaded` Certificates.
+ `type` (enum[string], optional) - Choose between uploading a Certificate in PEM format or requesting a managed *Let's Encrypt* Certificate. If omitted defaults to `uploaded`.
    + `uploaded`
    + `managed`


## CreateCertificateResponse (object)


### Properties
+ `action` (NullableAction, optional, nullable) 
+ `certificate` (Certificate, required) 


## NullableAction (object)


### Properties
+ `command`: `start_server` (string, required) - Command executed in the Action
+ `error` (Error, required, nullable) - Error message for the Action if error occurred, otherwise null
+ `finished`: `2016-01-30T23:55:00+00:00` (string, required, nullable) - Point in time when the Action was finished (in ISO-8601 format). Only set if the Action is finished otherwise null.
+ `id`: `42` (number, required) - ID of the Resource
+ `progress`: `100` (number, required) - Progress of Action in percent
+ `resources` (array[Resource], required) - Resources the Action relates to
+ `started`: `2016-01-30T23:55:00+00:00` (string, required) - Point in time when the Action was started (in ISO-8601 format)
+ `status` (enum[string], required) - Status of the Action
    + `success`
    + `running`
    + `error`


## CertificateResponse (object)


### Properties
+ `certificate` (Certificate, required) 


## UpdateCertificateRequest (object)


### Properties
+ `labels`: `{"labelkey":"value"}` (object, optional) - User-defined labels (key-value pairs)
+ `name`: `my website cert` (string, optional) - New Certificate name


## Datacenters Response (object)


### Properties
+ `datacenters` (array[Datacenter], required) 
+ `recommendation`: `1` (number, required) - The Datacenter which is recommended to be used to create new Servers.


## Datacenter (object)


### Properties
+ `description`: `Falkenstein DC Park 8` (string, required) - Description of the Datacenter
+ `id`: `42` (number, required) - ID of the Resource
+ `location` (Location, required) 
+ `name`: `fsn1-dc8` (string, required) - Unique identifier of the Datacenter
+ `server_types` (ServerTypes, required) - The Server types the Datacenter can handle


## Location (object)


### Properties
+ `city`: `Falkenstein` (string, required) - City the Location is closest to
+ `country`: `DE` (string, required) - ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 code of the country the Location resides in
+ `description`: `Falkenstein DC Park 1` (string, required) - Description of the Location
+ `id`: `1` (number, required) - ID of the Location
+ `latitude`: `50.47612` (number, required) - Latitude of the city closest to the Location
+ `longitude`: `12.370071` (number, required) - Longitude of the city closest to the Location
+ `name`: `fsn1` (string, required) - Unique identifier of the Location
+ `network_zone`: `eu-central` (string, required) - Name of network zone this Location resides in


## ServerTypes (object)
The Server types the Datacenter can handle

### Properties
+ `available`: `[1,2,3]` (array[number], required) - IDs of Server types that are supported and for which the Datacenter has enough resources left
+ `available_for_migration`: `[1,2,3]` (array[number], required) - IDs of Server types that are supported and for which the Datacenter has enough resources left
+ `supported`: `[1,2,3]` (array[number], required) - IDs of Server types that are supported in the Datacenter


## Datacenters Response1 (object)


### Properties
+ `datacenter` (Datacenter, required) 


## FirewallsResponse (object)


### Properties
+ `firewalls` (array[Firewall], required) 
+ `meta` (Meta, optional) 


## Firewall (object)


### Properties
