## LoadBalancerServiceHealthCheck (object)
Service health check

### Properties
+ `http` (Http, optional) - Additional configuration for protocol http
+ `interval`: `15` (number, required) - Time interval in seconds health checks are performed
+ `port`: `4711` (number, required) - Port the health check will be performed on
+ `protocol` (enum[string], required) - Type of the health check
    + `tcp`
    + `http`
+ `retries`: `3` (number, required) - Unsuccessful retries needed until a target is considered unhealthy; an unhealthy target needs the same number of successful retries to become healthy again
+ `timeout`: `10` (number, required) - Time in seconds after an attempt is considered a timeout


## Http (object)
Additional configuration for protocol http

### Properties
+ `domain`: `example.com` (string, required, nullable) - Host header to send in the HTTP request. May not contain spaces, percent or backslash symbols. Can be null, in that case no host header is sent.
+ `path`: `/` (string, required) - HTTP path to use for health checks. May not contain literal spaces, use percent-encoding instead.
+ `response`: `{"status":"ok"}` (string, optional) - String that must be contained in HTTP response in order to pass the health check
+ `status_codes`: `["2??","3??"]` (array[string], optional) - List of returned HTTP status codes in order to pass the health check. Supports the wildcards `?` for exactly one character and `*` for multiple ones. The default is to pass the health check for any status code between 2?? and 3??.
+ `tls`: `false` (boolean, optional) - Use HTTPS for health check


## LoadBalancerServiceHTTP (object)
Configuration option for protocols http and https

### Properties
+ `certificates`: `[897]` (array[number], optional) - IDs of the Certificates to use for TLS/SSL termination by the Load Balancer; empty for TLS/SSL passthrough or if `protocol` is "http"
+ `cookie_lifetime`: `300` (number, optional) - Lifetime of the cookie used for sticky sessions
+ `cookie_name`: `HCLBSTICKY` (string, optional) - Name of the cookie used for sticky sessions
+ `redirect_http`: `true` (boolean, optional) - Redirect HTTP requests to HTTPS. Only available if protocol is "https". Default `false`
+ `sticky_sessions`: `true` (boolean, optional) - Use sticky sessions. Only available if protocol is "http" or "https". Default `false`


