## Server18 (object)


### Properties
+ `backup_window`: `22-02` (string, required, nullable) - Time window (UTC) in which the backup will run, or null if the backups are not enabled
+ `created`: `2016-01-30T23:55:00+00:00` (string, required) - Point in time when the Resource was created (in ISO-8601 format)
+ `datacenter` (Datacenter6, required) - Datacenter this Resource is located at
+ `id`: `42` (number, required) - ID of the Resource
+ `image` (Image, required, nullable) 
+ `included_traffic`: `654321` (number, required, nullable) - Free Traffic for the current billing period in bytes
+ `ingoing_traffic`: `123456` (number, required, nullable) - Inbound Traffic for the current billing period in bytes
+ `iso` (Iso2, required, nullable) - ISO Image that is attached to this Server. Null if no ISO is attached.
+ `labels` (string, required) - User-defined labels (key-value pairs)
+ `load_balancers` (array[number], optional) 
+ `locked`: `false` (boolean, required) - True if Server has been locked and is not available to user
+ `name`: `my-resource` (string, required) - Name of the Server (must be unique per Project and a valid hostname as per RFC 1123)
+ `outgoing_traffic`: `123456` (number, required, nullable) - Outbound Traffic for the current billing period in bytes
+ `placement_group` (PlacementGroupNullable, optional, nullable) 
+ `primary_disk_size`: `50` (number, required) - Size of the primary Disk
+ `private_net` (array[PrivateNet4], required) - Private networks information
+ `protection` (Protection20, required) - Protection configuration for the Server
+ `public_net` (PublicNet4, required) - Public network information. The Server's IPv4 address can be found in `public_net->ipv4->ip`
+ `rescue_enabled`: `false` (boolean, required) - True if rescue mode is enabled. Server will then boot into rescue system on next reboot
+ `server_type` (ServerType1, required) - Type of Server - determines how much ram, disk and cpu a Server has
+ `status` (enum[string], required) - Status of the Server
    + `running`
    + `initializing`
    + `starting`
    + `stopping`
    + `off`
    + `deleting`
    + `migrating`
    + `rebuilding`
    + `unknown`
+ `volumes` (array[number], optional) - IDs of Volumes assigned to this Server


