+ `blocked`: `false` (boolean, required) - If the IP is blocked by our anti abuse dept
+ `dns_ptr`: `server01.example.com` (string, required) - Reverse DNS PTR entry for the IPv4 addresses of this Server
+ `id`: `42` (number, optional) - ID of the Resource
+ `ip`: `1.2.3.4` (string, required) - IP address (v4) of this Server


## Ipv64 (object)
IPv6 network assigned to this Server and its reverse DNS entry

### Properties
+ `blocked`: `false` (boolean, required) - If the IP is blocked by our anti abuse dept
+ `dns_ptr` (array[DnsPtr8], required, nullable) - Reverse DNS PTR entries for the IPv6 addresses of this Server, `null` by default
+ `id`: `42` (number, optional) - ID of the Resource
+ `ip`: `2001:db8::/64` (string, required) - IP address (v6) of this Server


## DnsPtr8 (object)


### Properties
+ `dns_ptr`: `server.example.com` (string, required) - DNS pointer for the specific IP address
+ `ip`: `2001:db8::1` (string, required) - Single IPv6 address of this Server for which the reverse DNS entry has been set up


## ServerType1 (object)
Type of Server - determines how much ram, disk and cpu a Server has

### Properties
+ `cores`: `1` (number, required) - Number of cpu cores a Server of this type will have
+ `cpu_type` (enum[string], required) - Type of cpu
    + `shared`
    + `dedicated`
+ `deprecated`: `false` (boolean, required) - True if Server type is deprecated
+ `description`: `CX11` (string, required) - Description of the Server type
+ `disk`: `25` (number, required) - Disk size a Server of this type will have in GB
+ `id`: `1` (number, required) - ID of the Server type
+ `memory`: `1` (number, required) - Memory a Server of this type will have in GB
+ `name`: `cx11` (string, required) - Unique identifier of the Server type
+ `prices` (array[Price9], required) - Prices in different Locations
+ `storage_type` (enum[string], required) - Type of Server boot drive. Local has higher speed. Network has better availability.
    + `local`
    + `network`


## CreateServerRequest (object)


### Properties
+ `automount`: `false` (boolean, optional) - Auto-mount Volumes after attach
+ `datacenter`: `nbg1-dc3` (string, optional) - ID or name of Datacenter to create Server in (must not be used together with location)
+ `firewalls` (array[Firewall4], optional) - Firewalls which should be applied on the Server's public network interface at creation time
+ `image`: `ubuntu-20.04` (string, required) - ID or name of the Image the Server is created from
+ `labels` (object, optional) - User-defined labels (key-value pairs)
+ `location`: `nbg1` (string, optional) - ID or name of Location to create Server in (must not be used together with datacenter)
+ `name`: `my-server` (string, required) - Name of the Server to create (must be unique per Project and a valid hostname as per RFC 1123)
+ `networks`: `[456]` (array[number], optional) - Network IDs which should be attached to the Server private network interface at the creation time
+ `placement_group`: `1` (number, optional) - ID of the Placement Group the server should be in
+ `public_net` (PublicNet5, optional) - Public Network options
+ `server_type`: `cx11` (string, required) - ID or name of the Server type this Server should be created with
+ `ssh_keys`: `["my-ssh-key"]` (array[string], optional) - SSH key IDs (`integer`) or names (`string`) which should be injected into the Server at creation time
+ `start_after_create`: `true` (boolean, optional) - Start Server right after creation. Defaults to true.
+ `user_data`: `#cloud-config
runcmd:
- [touch, /root/cloud-init-worked]` (string, optional) - Cloud-Init user data to use during Server creation. This field is limited to 32KiB.
+ `volumes`: `[123]` (array[number], optional) - Volume IDs which should be attached to the Server at the creation time. Volumes must be in the same Location.


## Firewall4 (object)


### Properties
+ `firewall` (number, optional) - ID of the Firewall


## PublicNet5 (object)
Public Network options

### Properties
+ `enable_ipv4` (boolean, optional) - Attach an IPv4 on the public NIC. If false, no IPv4 address will be attached. Defaults to true.
+ `enable_ipv6` (boolean, optional) - Attach an IPv6 on the public NIC. If false, no IPv6 address will be attached. Defaults to true.
+ `ipv4` (number, optional, nullable) - ID of the ipv4 Primary IP to use. If omitted and enable_ipv4 is true, a new ipv4 Primary IP will automatically be created.
+ `ipv6` (number, optional, nullable) - ID of the ipv6 Primary IP to use. If omitted and enable_ipv6 is true, a new ipv6 Primary IP will automatically be created.


